Package: hbart
Type: Package
Title: Heteroscedastic Bayesian Additive Regression Trees
Version: 1.0
Date: 2019-07-28
Authors@R: c(person('Robert', 'McCulloch', role=c('aut','cre','cph'),email='robert.e.mcculloch@gmail.com'),
  person('Matthew', 'Pratola', role=c('aut','cph')), person('Hugh','Chipman',role=c('aut','cph')))
Description: The model Y = f(x) + s(x) Z is fit where functions f and s are ensembles of trees and Z is standard normal. This model is described in 'Heteroscedastic BART Via Multiplicative Regression Trees' (Pratola, Chipman, George, and McCulloch 2020) <doi:10.1080/10618600.2019.1677243>. The predictor vector x may be high dimensional. A Markov Chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) algorithm provides Bayesian posterior uncertainty for both f and s. Efficient MCMC is based on recent innovations in proposal mechanisms for Bayesian regression tree models (Pratola 2015) <doi:10.1214/16-BA999>. This is a C++ header-only implementation that mimics the rbart package on CRAN.
